President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals to serve on the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System. Stanley Fischer was nominated to serve as Vice Chairman and Governor, Lael Brainard was nominated to serve as Governor, and Jerome Powell was nominated for a second term as Governor. President Obama praised their experience and knowledge of the financial system. Stanley Fischer has served as the Governor of the Bank of Israel and Vice Chairman of Citigroup. Lael Brainard was the U.S. Department of the Treasury's Under Secretary for International Affairs and Vice President of the Brookings Institution. Jerome Powell has been a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve since 2012 and has previous experience at The Carlyle Group and the Department of the Treasury.